<reference id="enum_audiosessionoperationrestriction">
    <title><ph keyref="AUDIO_SESSION_OPERATION_RESTRICTION"/></title>
    <shortdesc id="short"><ph id="shortdesc">The operation permissions of the SDK on the audio session.</ph></shortdesc>
    <refbody>
        <section id="parameters">
            <title>Enumerator</title>
            <parml>
            <plentry>
                <pt><ph keyref="AUDIO_SESSION_OPERATION_RESTRICTION_NONE"/></pt>
                <pd>No restriction, the SDK can change the audio session.</pd>
            </plentry>
            <plentry>
                <pt><ph keyref="AUDIO_SESSION_OPERATION_RESTRICTION_SET_CATEGORY"/></pt>
                <pd>The SDK cannot change the audio session category.</pd>
            </plentry>
            <plentry>
                <pt><ph keyref="AUDIO_SESSION_OPERATION_RESTRICTION_CONFIGURE_SESSION"/></pt>
                <pd>The SDK cannot change the audio session category, mode, or categoryOptions.</pd>
            </plentry>
            <plentry>
                <pt><ph keyref="AUDIO_SESSION_OPERATION_RESTRICTION_DEACTIVATE_SESSION"/></pt>
                <pd>The SDK keeps the audio session active when the user leaves the channel, for example, to play an audio file in the background.</pd>
            </plentry>
            <plentry>
                <pt><ph keyref="AUDIO_SESSION_OPERATION_RESTRICTION_ALL"/></pt>
                <pd>Completely restricts the operation permissions of the SDK on the audio session; the SDK cannot change the audio session.</pd>
            </plentry>
            </parml> </section>
    </refbody>
</reference>
